parameters:
Oh, Konoha-chan, you've come here often! I'm
very... very happy about it!

I came here as promised. So, is this the guild
reception?

That's right! This is the reception of the
\C[2]Magical Girl Guild\C[0]!

This guild is responsible for various tasks such
as quests that only magical girls can undertake,
managing the houses to protect magical girls, and
many other things.
I see. Well, can I ask you a few things for now?
Please feel free to ask me anything, Konoha-chan!
What is the Magical Girl Guild?
What is this world? I wonder what it's called.

This is a massive island known as \C[3]Grimoire
Land\C[0]...

It is said that it was originally part of the
Raderial continent, but in ancient times, it was
separated from the southern end of the continent
by a great power and has remained so until now.

An island... So there's also a continent? Can we
go there too?

Well, you see, in the northern mountains or if you
go out to sea from this island, you can't go
towards the continent... because there is a space
where living creatures cannot inhabit that has
been set up...

This island is what you would call... a secluded
island... shrouded in mystery.

So, who is in charge of managing this Grimoire
Land?

Originally, this island was governed by Lord
Candira, the ruler of this town... However, as
time passed, it became difficult to govern the
entire island...

Currently, the four regions outside of this town
are managed by a race called the Lolimon.
Lolimon... Monsters? Are they an enemy force?

Oh no, not at all! The Lolimon are our allies,
generally speaking!

We are opposing the demons by borrowing the power
of the four Lolimon leaders in those towns.

That's right. If we can borrow the power of the
Lolimon leaders in each region, it should become a
considerably effective force.

And since we can welcome regular Lolimon as
allies, I definitely want you to make them your
allies.

So, what about this place? They mentioned
something about a Magical Girl Guild...

Yes, let me explain in detail. This guild can be
considered the heart of the Rein Garnet town.

By joining this guild, you will gain the right to
live in the guild house (base) and the right to
accept guild quests.

At the guild house, you can prepare and use the
item box, of course. It's also very important for
resting and recovering.

Regarding the guild house, there is a caretaker
there, so it would be good if you could ask them
about various things! (From here, it is located to
the southeast.)

So, guild quests are mainly special quests that
only magical girls can undertake.
Quests that only magical girls can undertake?

Basically, the majority of quests are Demon
Extermination quests. Since only magical girls
have the means to counter demons, these types of
quests are gathered in this guild.

So, this guild fully backs up and supports us for
those kinds of battles, right?

That's right! Your quick understanding is greatly
appreciated... Truly, you are the savior...

What is that enemy? It seemed different from the
usual monsters in terms of atmosphere.

Mmm, sharp observation! Indeed, that enemy is
called \C[10]Demon\C[0], and they are the
archenemy of both humans and the Lolimon tribe.

In a location northeast of Grimoire Land, there
exists a stronghold of demons. We have been
fighting against them for many years, that's the
current situation...

Are you always being attacked like that? You
endure it well...

Oh no, that was a rare case. It felt like we were
being attacked because the protective
\C[2]barrier\C[0] around the town was broken and
they managed to invade.

The power of the demons is unique, and it is
almost impossible for us humans to match them.
That's why the power of magical girls and the
Lolimon tribe is necessary...

Since there aren't that many magical girls in
existence, it's difficult to constantly protect
the town.

So, we have developed a barrier that can counter
the demons through years of research in
cooperation with the Lolimon tribe.

So, you're saying that the important barrier was
broken and invaded, and that's when I happened to
be reincarnated... into this world by chance?
Well, that's how it is... I'm really glad.

By the way, if we were to distinguish the enemy
forces, they would be divided into categories such
as Demons, Magical Beasts, and Bandits...
something like that.
It's not just demons, huh? That's tough.

Compared to demons, many of the 'magical beasts'
are relatively docile. Our attacks as humans can
also be effective against them, so they don't
usually go out of their way to invade.

The problem lies with those called Bandits...
These guys were originally human males... but they
became Bandits by selling their souls to the
demons.

Selling their souls to demons...!? What terrible
people they are.

Since it's not easy to tell just by appearance,
please be careful, Konoha-chan...

I still don't really understand, but what exactly
is a magical girl? What exactly is a magical girl?

Magical girls are said to be beings whose very
existence is considered to be sacred magical
power, and they are the only ones who can oppose
demons.

It seems that in order to be born, one must
undergo a sudden reincarnation from the sky...
This seems to be an unchanging law since ancient
times.
(For some reason, I became that magical girl...)

This time, Konoha-chan, you were reincarnated in
this town in that form, but originally, you should
have been born at a place called the Tower of
Reincarnation, which is built to the south of the
town...
Hmmm... The Tower of Reincarnation, huh?

The Tower of Reincarnation was built so that
reincarnated magical girls wouldn't get lost, but
this time, you appeared as if to save the town
from its crisis...
What else would you call this if not a savior?

It's really exaggerated. It's just a
coincidence...

(I wonder if it's really just a coincidence...
There are so many things I don't understand, like
the power I felt from this sword...)

(Now the question is... what should I do from
here?)

(Someone's words from my faint memories just
before coming here... Save us from the end. These
words seem to be some kind of key.)

Gilcho, I understand that magical girls protect
people from the terrifying demons.

Since I seem to be a magical girl too, there's
just one thing I want to ask before I agree to
cooperate...

Is there a possibility that this world is facing a
crisis of its end?

Why is that...? That is a prophecy of a certain
witch, you know.

It's said to be the Great Prophecy of the witch
Freya, and rumors are spreading in a certain town
that it will happen soon.

The beginning of the end is near, the world will
be forever sealed. The conclusion of the story is
the end itself.

The conclusion of the story is the end itself... I
wonder what that means.

There are many uncertainties, and it is said that
she just wants to confuse the people. The witch
Freya is known as a stubborn person, so...

Regardless of its authenticity, it might be better
not to get too close, I suppose.

(Hmm, it seems like there is a need to meet. I
want to clarify what I should do here.)
I guess that's all for the questions.

Lord Candira, who rules over this town, expressed
a strong desire to meet with you. So, I would like
you to go and meet him.

I think you will definitely receive a reward for
saving this town, so

Yes, I suppose it's important to greet him. I
understand. I'll go meet him later.

The Lord's mansion is located to the
\C[2]north\C[0] of the town, I believe.
